## Deployment

### Express Server (Standard)

The project runs as a standard Express server — **not serverless/Lambda**. Deployments target containers or VMs.

```bash
# Build & start
npm run build
npm run start

# Environment variables required at runtime
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...
REDIS_URL=redis://...
AWS_REGION=...
WHATSAPP_TOKEN=...
```

- Entry point: `src/index.ts` (or `src/server.ts`)
- The server binds to `process.env.PORT` (default 3000)
- Health check: `GET /health`

This document serves as the foundation for maintaining code quality and consistency across the DatiHub backend application. All team members should follow these practices to ensure a maintainable, scalable, and testable codebase.
